name: Larry S.
text:
My kids and I spent part of last week in Coloma Cottages, and we would highly recommend the Cottages. The location of the cottages is right on the river as advertised and the grounds of the cottages is very nice and comfortable for adults or kids. Also, the location is really just a 5 minute walk to the historic town, and very conveniently located for us to go rafting and enjoy the area.

The cottage we stayed in was the Rio Azul, and it was both very clean and comfortable for my family. The rooms and bedrooms were great and the kitchen was easy to cook dinner in.

I give them 5 stars.

text:
DO NOT STAY HERE! Pay an extra ten bucks and stay a couple of hotels down.

I have stayed at many Days Inns thru out the US. I find these Hotels to be a nice stay for the value. Usually clean rooms, good customer service, and clean linen. But this Hotel was dirty, Horrible customer service and dirty linen. The room was Hot and uncomfortable to sleep. The sheets were dirty with food spots and other soils. The Carpet was also dirty with spots. Wires were exposed in the wall.

I called to be changed to another room and they told me they couldn't because they were full, which was not true. I stayed here for three days and pre-paid and they wouldn't give me a refund. Next time I would totally pay an extra 10 bucks and stay at another hotel.

I will never stay at this hotel again and I do not recommend anybody else to stay here.

name: Steve Arias
text: Wow. This place is Run Down! Let me just start by saying we had reservations but when we checked in they said price went up...we were here on a big mountain bike event and there was no rooms available elsewhere. Beds were nasty and forced us to go to Wal-Mart and buy sleeping bags. Inside of the rooms are falling apart.. burn marks on comforters. Carpet looked like they were slashed with a blade. TV was super snowy and direct tv was a joke. Only one channel worked for us. Called reception and it rang another room. Also, seems like there is long term residents here. Outside of building is falling apart as well and seems like no one cleans at all. There was trash everywhere. Roof is falling apart and missing shingles. This place needs a major make over with large investment or a wrecking ball.

name: Miles Martin
text:
This place is dirty, no filthy, and the
entire property is littered with garbage and cigarette butts. I was there when The Monterey County Health Dept.had red tagged the pool, locked it with their pad lock and had put a big warning sign on the entrance to the pool and jaccuzzi.

The carpets are so dirty that your white socks get black just walking around the room after a short period of time.

Musty rooms with boken microwaves, wires hanging out, wrecked cars and PODS in the parking lot, cig burns in the blankets, lumpy pillows on old mattresses,  beer cans and trash found under the bed, bare bones breakfast lacking anything remotely good for you, suspect people roaming the parking lot at night, etc. etc, etc..

Even the staff laugh at what they're asking for the rooms !!

And the older Eastern Indian lady in the office had such a short fuse that when confronted with the health and safety violations on the property and overall cleanliness of the pool and property, she sent her punk ass husband out to to threaten to "kick my ass." Really ?

AVOID THIS PLACE !!!!

name: Brett Chik
text:
The hotel has been closed since December but reopened recently and we started on the first night it was open.

The good:
- The service was amazing. Everyone we interacted with had the utmost level of professionalism. The doormen greeted me by name each time we came and went which was a really nice touch.
- The room had an incredible view of the Bay.
- Room service was very quick.
- Staff was very fast to respond to the Four Seasons in-app messaging.
- Everything was clean and modern.
- The crab and shrimp omelette was delicious.
- Wireless charger and USB ports on the nightstand was a nice touch.

The bad:
- The was no in-room dining menu in our room nor any instructions on where to find one. We had to ask for a link to the menu.
- The coffee was absolutely terrible.  I‚Äôm not exaggerating when I say it was some the worst I have ever had my life.  After disliking it in one meal, they provided it complimentary in another meal but it was still quite bad. The problem likely isn‚Äôt the preparation but rather the selected beans. SF has a number of amazing roasters, they should seek out a better option from a local roaster.
- Doors slamming all morning long. I don‚Äôt know if it was Staff or guests, but from around 8 am too 11 am, doors near our room were constantly being opened and closed and quite loudly.  This woke me up and prevented me from getting as much sleep as I wanted to.  The doors need to be assisted so they close quietly.
- The toilet paper was completely awful, very thin and quite abrasive. This was so pretty surprising detail and I can‚Äôt begin to imagine how the product they were using would even be considered remotely up to their standards.

Overall, it wasn‚Äôt too bad but I don‚Äôt think it lived up to their reputation. I know they recently reopened and there are mistakes to be expected but something like low quality toilet paper doesn‚Äôt really have an excuse.  I hope this review will allow them the opportunity to make improvements where there are currently deficits.

I‚Äôm not sure I would stay there again at that price point given the above issues.

name: Yamami Studios
text:
Loews Regency San Francisco is a deluxe 5-star spa San Francisco city center hotel steps from Wells Fargo History Museum and within a short walk of Union Square. Staying here, you'll also be within a short walk of TransAmerica Pyramid and San Francisco Museum of Modern Art. This building is the third tallest in the city and offers a great view of the city.

The staff is amazing and friendly, ready to accommodate us for our every need.

This hotel has its own restaurant serving breakfast, lunch and dinner where you'll find a selection of items to try. Escape the stress of everyday life at The Spa, offering facials and body scrubs, as well as Swedish massages, deep-tissue massages and hot stone massages. Guests wishing to enjoy a drink will surely want to visit the bar/lounge.
In addition to the on-site spa, leisure facilities on offer include a 24-hour fitness center. Guests can make use of the free WiFi.

name: Guthrie Paterson
text: Great business hotel in the Financial District.  Rooms and service are great!  Also a good place for a breakfast meeting.

name: Md Sajjad Zahid
text:
Occupying the top 11 floors of a 48-floor high-rise in the Financial District, this contemporary, high-end hotel is a 5-minute walk from both the Embarcadero BART station and the Transamerica Pyramid.

Sophisticated, modern rooms feature 47-inch flat-screen TVs, iPod docks and Italian linens, plus picture windows offering views of the city or the Golden Gate Bridge. Upgraded rooms have marble bathrooms with separate tubs and showers. Suites add living rooms; some have terraces. There's 24-hour room service.

Amenities include a spa, a 24-hour business center and a gym, along with a warm bar and a polished brasserie serving Californian cuisine.

name: Mildred Griffin
text: We stayed 4 nights at the Loews Regency in the business district of San Francisco. We were greeted by the doorman and the front desk very warmly when we arrived. We were then taken to our room on the 47th floor with the most beautiful views on the bay from the Golden Gate Bridge, Sausilito, Alcatraz, to the lit up Bay Bridge. Unbelievable. The service at all levels is over the top and always with smiles. The best in SF and we have stayed all over SF the last 25 years We will be back

name: Brandon S
text:
The free breakfast consisted of recently thawed Eggo waffles... like still soggy levels of thaw just sitting out in the open. The fruit and bagels were decent enough but it felt more like a break room for employees than anything I'd consider to be for guests. No employees present, just a few guests, a few tables, and some snack foods tossed together.

The hand towel in the bathroom had a rather dark stain on it, I'm assuming from the last guest that put it back well enough the cleaning staff didn't bother checking. The overall cleanliness of the room was suspect...I found hair in the bed that wasn't mine.

Overall for what it cost for the night it was adequate, if the above doesn't bother you of course.

name: Lisa F
text: Friendly staff, good location away from the craziness of the convention center. I found the room to be clean with a nice big fridge and comfy bed. The lights freaked me out a few times until I figured out how to turn the sensors off. An important thing to know about this area is it gets very loud outside on the weekend nights, there is a billiard hall and a couple nightclubs with loud people and motorcycles. If you want to get any sleep friday or saturday night before 2am bring earplugs and tylenol pm. Across the street from the front desk there is a bakery that has the most amazing cream puffs and other treats. You can't beat the free parking, that is what always brings me back here during conventions, they lock the parking lot up at night for anyone who doesn't have a key so I felt safe walking back to my room after dark.

name: TJ Taylor
text:
This is a wonderful hotel with a beautiful view of a lake.  The staff is very friendly and the cleaning of the rooms are daily.  The rooms are spacious and business grade.  You have free wi-fi, ice, central heating/air, clean linen, adjustable beds (sleep number), coffee maker, alarm clock radio, hair dryer, shampoo, conditioner, lotion and soap.  The view of the lake was grand with a fountain, geese on the water, a Koi fish pond with it's own fountain and a nice pathway.  The hotel also has a swimming pool with a safety fence a small amphitheater area with soft music coming through speakers when not in use. There are ice rooms located around the property with soda machines.

The convention rooms are elegant and host many events. There is a Grill that serves and offers room service, a Bar but my favorite is the dining room.  The breakfasts were fresh cooked daily whether it was served or buffet and refilled often.  The morning servers along with the chef and cooks were very friendly and personable. They were my favorite part of the experience not excluding Sylvia at the front desk.

The rooms are very clean along with their bathrooms. Because of the fear of bed bugs in some of the local motels and extended stay hotels this was a pleasant experience. alleviating those concerns. All concerns are addressed immediately (not that there should be any but things can happen).

Do be aware that during the wet season it tended to flood in front of the entrance to the hotel's property. (This might have been addressed by now)

This hotel is a definite Yes and a Must Try.

The hotel is in a strange area but it very close to to downtown, Arden Fair, business 80 freeway and lots of restaurants and shopping. The hotel is a good value, but needs some work.

text:
I wasn't sure what to expect with the price and some of the reviews I read.  However, I was very pleasantly surprised by how cute it is and how nice the room was.  Sure, it's an older motel so the bathrooms aren't luxurious or big, but the room itself was very nice with the laminate wood floor and updated furniture.  It felt clean and modern.

For the price and quality I fully recommend this place to everyone looking for a low cost way to have a place in Palm Springs.  If you don't need the big pool vibe and just want a clean, pretty place to sleep you cannot go wrong here.

name: Lisa H.
text: This hotel was fantastic. It is a small property, but the staff is super friendly and helpful. The pool area is so relaxing... It is located in a great location. The rooms are newly renovated, really well maintained, and very clean.

name: Roy Steele
text:
I had a three night stay at The Monroe Palm Springs. I wasn't familiar with this three star hotel in North Palm Springs, and stumbling upon it was pure luck on my part.  The check in was quick and easy, and the front desk staff were efficient and friendly. They were able to answer my questions about the hotel and restaurants in the immediate vicinity. This is a limited service hotel as they don't have a restaurant on property.

I had a room with a king sized bed at the back of the property. The room was spacious, the bed and pillows were comfortable, the wifi was adequate, and the bathroom was clean. I didn't leave the a/c on when I wasn't in the room, so most importantly, the air conditioning was fantastic and cooled the room quickly. I also appreciated the large HDTV.

The pool area and jacuzzi faces south, so it's perfect for sun bathing.

This old Ramada Inn was renovated by the current owner, and they did a brilliant job. The interior designers transformed this tired chain hotel into a unique and hip boutique hotel. I would stay at The Monroe Palm Springs again without hesitation.

name: Dana Chef
text:
Although they are going through renovations,  the rooms were clean and nice. The staff was friendly and accommodating!
I came for a quiet, relaxing getaway, and met my objective!

text: Rooms a bit small but cozy. No ice machine? Shower head came off mid shower but quickly replaced it with no further issue.

text: Rafael at the front desk was friendly and helpful, so was the housekeeping staff. The room were very clean, nice, and liked the floors. For the price definitely better than the other options.

text: I luv luv luv luv this place. Super cute inside and out. It was the hilton a few years back and a days inn before that. I think its going to change owners again but either way the name may change often but its always been a nice clean friendly warm comfortable place throughout the years.

name: Chris Jefferson
text: I would not recommend that anyone stay here. Not one thing was correct during my time at the hotel.  There was insufficient parking.  I did not get the room I requested.  The widely advertised remodel had only taken place in a few rooms, not in all of them as they would have you believe, and my bed was broken....yeah.

name: Mary Falls
text:
We stayed for two days during the week.
The good - The room was nice. The bed was comfortable and the pillows were fluffy.
The bad - The ice machine was broken the whole time we were there. The staff told us to walk to 7 eleven if we needed ice. The jacuzzi was broken. The staff said it would be fixed the day we checked out. There were fire ants in the pool area and when we let the staff know, all that was said was "oh great. I'll let maintenance know." There was really only one staff member that was worth remembering.

In our opinion, this is not a place that is very accommodating. If you just need a place to sleep, this is the place.

text: Good value. Nice clean room. Only spent one night for a place to sleep. Didn't see around the property much.

text:
Basic hotel in the Northern part of Palm Springs, with easy access to Downtown (5 mins by car). We liked our comfortable beds and the cleanliness of the rooms.

We did not get to try the pool as we only stayed one night and arrived pretty late. If you consider this hotel for your stay in Palm Springs make sure to check coupon websites before booking as they seem to offer a Groupon every once in awhile. Without discount the room rate is a little bit over what you'd expect to pay for a standard two-story hotel.

name: Michael Thomson
text:
I have stayed at many hotels around the world, having worked for The Four Seasons Hotels and Resorts for many years in management.  I know what a value is when I see it.  Due to a fire in my home I needed a place to stay.  Having lived in Palm Springs for over 20 years, I watched as this hotel like most things in Palm Springs was brought back to life.  I never imagined it would be so nice and at such a great price.  Beats the heck out of Motel 6.  Better ptice, much nicer room, free wifi ($2.99 a day at Motel 6) and a free breakfast.  Not just a contintal breakfast or just coffee, but a real breakfast.  In a real restaurant with real servers and some of the best food in town.  Rick's has always been a favorite of my Late husband and myself.  If you are even thinking of staying anywhere else, STOP, look and listen, this is THE only place hands down.
Michael Thomson

Asked her about it and she made a point to tell me that she had to come back TWICE! Look I shouldn't even have to ask in the first place! Finally got one and the coffee was terrible! Frustrating! The pictures of the rooms online are not what you get at all! I was wanting bright and cheery like the pics and got dreary and dreadful! The ice machine was disgusting and not usable! text:
My stay was extremely pleasant. I was only suppose to stay for 4 days however, my stay turned into two weeks.
Being that my reservations were for only 4 days they were able to find me a room for the remaining of my stay. The first room was big and roomy. Room 205. The second room had a balcony which the view was beautiful. Lush green trees, peaceful, Room 209.  What I really appreciated so much is that they allowed me to take care of my mom's service dog. My mom fractured her hip and could not take care of her pooch. I explained the situation and they allowed me to bring my mom's pooch to stay with me. They were so understanding, it was incredible, and meant so much to both my mom and myself. This really goes above and beyond. All of the staff are so nice. I would highly  recommend this hotel. This is the only hotel I will ever stay in when I am in Sebastopol.

text: Room was large but older looking. Had a kitchen with a stove top, 2 microwaves because the built in didn't work. Beds we're comfortable. Location was beyond perfect. Close walk to the beach and close to some good restaurants. Service was okay. Breakfast was minimal. There is construction going on so expect banging and sawing during the day hours. Location was perfect but the rest left something to be desired.

text: Room was spacious but kitchenette not working.  Hairdryer not working.  Got replacement.  Very comfortable beds.  Breakfast served in a very small and tight spot and not the greatest, coffee and OJ from machine.  In San Francisco, you get your money's worth here since every place is so pricey.

text: Very clean place. Everyone was so nice and the price was affordable. I will be coming back for my next vacation.

name: Christopher Matthews
text:
In short, this is an overpriced 2 star hotel.

We stayed on the ground floor. The room was nicer than Motel 6, but not $200/night nicer. Neighbors doors could be heard closing. Upstairs neighbors sounded lime a herd of elephants. Parking is bizarre, being underground and not well lit, plus no elevator from the bottom. For the money, you might expect more than plastic-wrapped grocery store danishes, bad coffee, apple and orange juices, toast, and apples and oranges. Maybe should have cereal, cocoa, more fruit options, yogurts, bagels, etc. Half the electrical plugs wouldn't hold the pins for our phone chargers amd the plugs are difficult to get to. No pool.

On the plus side, it's four blocks from the beach and across the street from the San Francisco Zoo and just a couple miles to the VA Medical Center. The beds aren't high end, but they are relatively comfortable. It's probably worth $100/night, but that's it.

name: Rose Deleonardo
text:
Isn't near the San Francisco sites most people want to see. We had to take an Uber back & forth. It didn't have an elevator to the upper floors, so you have to lug your suitcases up &down stairs by yourself. Complimentary breakfast exists solely of coffe, tea, juice & packaged danishes. Even 1/2 of the toaster didn't work. There's no main room to eat, so you have to juggle your food & drink up the stairs to your room or make several trips.
The manager Amy, who's probably a relative, was arrogant & rude on several occasions to my sister-in-law.
resp:
Hi Rose,
We're so sorry to hear about your negative experience at Mirage Inn and Suites and hope you will give us a second chance to show you the kind of service we are capable of.
Thank you,
The Mirage Team

text: This is my absolute favorite place to stay in Palm Springs. The owners Rick and Rob greet you with a hug and know you by your name upon check in. Continental breakfast is served daily with a variety of cereals, muffins, donuts, breakfast bars, milk, coffee, bananas, oatmeal, etc. Since I‚Äôm a foodie, my favorite part of the resort is during a 3 day weekend stay, they do a bbq for the entire resort. text: Just spent 5 wonderful days. Large, spacious rooms nicely done. Ours included a full kitchen. Recently upgraded grounds are very relaxing. Our hosts took great care to see to our needs. If you are looking for a men's resort close to everything,  this should be your destination!

name: Anthony Minier (DJ AnthonyM)
text: This is a very comfortable enclosed gay men's resort. It is surrounded by high walls and the entry is through the check-in area so the owners (they live onsite) maintain some control over who is coming and going. This makes it one of the more mellow and quite resorts in this area and unless you are in your early 20's, you will appreciate the relaxed and easy going pace of this resort. The residences (studio's and suites) are in older buildings but they are well maintained and the whole complex has a certain charm to it. I have stayed here 3 times over the past so many years and have always enjoyed my visit immensely. They have a nice outdoor pool area which is clothing optional which also makes the high walls that surround the resort more useful since families driving by with children in their cars will not get an eyeful. There is a very large Jacuzzi as well. If you are gay and are visiting Palm Springs but the thought of the larger less intimate resorts that are often packed with a boisterous younger crowd don't quite appeal to your idea of a relaxing getaway, by all means try to book a room here. They are often fully booked since it is on the smaller side but you will be happy you stayed here if you book far enough in advance (or off season).

name: smith Aaron
text: My boyfriend and I stayed here for our trip out to LA and we couldn't have chosen a better place to stay. We stayed in the Abbot Kinney Suite, and it was a great experience. The suite had an open separate bedroom with desk and dresser with night tables on each side and a living room with a fire place. There was a cute kitchen with a deep sink and a claw foot tub and nicely tiled bathroom. The suite had windows everywhere and had massive amounts of sunlight. When you stepped out there was a balcony that overlooked Rose Ave and Venice Beach. (BEAUTIFUL) We sat our there often drinking and enjoying the view and atmosphere of Venice. The staff and owner were super nice and accommodating. The street was semi busy during the day and quite at night. There is a lot of restaurants around and the boardwalk is only steps away. The street parking was great. We always found a spot in front of the hotel. We came there to visit all of LA but just ended up stay in the area and keeping The Rose as our home base. Totally recommend staying here if you want to be away from all the crazy of the city and live like a local.

name: Matthew Morgan
text: Was reluctant to book here, due to other reviews.  Was pleasantly surprised.  Although you can tell that the rooms are old, they have done a respectable job renovating the rooms.  The heart shaped Jacuzzi is an awesome feature and it is big enough to comfortably accommodate two people.  The rooms were clean. New carpet and beds would make a big difference. Overall we were satisfied for the price we paid.  Microwave, refrigerator and a flat screen TV were nice new renovations.  The imitation fireplace was a very nice touch, had realistic animated flames and it put out some really good heat.  Was happy that there was a CVS and a Savemart next door and another great restaurant right down by the lake. (you can even see the lake from your back window upstairs).  If you are looking for a place that is kept clean for a good price, with a quaint atmosphere, this is where you should book.  We booked on Orbitz and saved a bundle with a coupon.

name: Laurie Swanson
text: Thankfully we only needed the room for the night. We are California residents doing business nearby and decided stay for the evening rather than fight the rush hour traffic back to San Diego. The O.C Fair has caused rooms to be limited. The only reason I am succumbing to posting a negative review is to perhaps save someone who has saved long for a vacation from utter disappointment! The owners of this establishment should be ashamed of not only the run down but  the filthy condition of their establishment. When entering the first room assigned to us we found it had not even been cleaned from the previous occupants! Potato chips strewn all over the floor, soiled bed and other debris strewn throughout the room. They upgraded us. Laughable. Keep in mind I do not mind staying at the Super 8 for overnights, I do not require the Ritz Carlton for practical matters. The upgrade to the "suite" the kitchen had a missing cabinet door, one of the two, broken glass in the Windows, the entry door had been kicked in and poorly patched and everything was disgustingly dirty, coffee table hasn't been wiped down in 20 years kind of grime! Just saying. And Im being nice.

text: Great value. Very good free breakfast. Nice rooms.

name: Natalie McManus
text: A bit old, definitely not in perfect condition, but good parking considering the area. Easy check in/out. Very comfortable bed. We had room 123, which is right next to the exit gate. It was pretty loud each time someone left. Very close to LAX and I would stay here again if I have any early flight.

name: Bill Tzetzos
text:
If I could give a zero, I would... Paper thin walls and directly under an LAX runway... What a dive. We can hear the people above and on either side. The next door shower sounds like it's in our bedroom.
Why bother renovating this dive. A waste of redecorating dollars.  @Wyndham... Drop this place and your overall rating will go up significantly. I'm actually thinking of dropping Wyndham as a chain where I may stay.

text: A little shady looking on the outside but an overall acceptable hotel to stay 1 quick night. The airplane traffic stopped around 11pm the night we were there. My kids (ages 4,6,&8) loved watching the jets come in to land every 5 minutes others may not enjoy it so much.

name: Katiria Perez
text: Got a nice clean room here. Will definitely stay again.

text: Clean, comfortable and stylish!!  Reasonably priced. Staff is super friendly! Would definitely stay there again.

name: April Rorie
text: Clean, comfortable and stylish!!  Reasonably priced. Staff is super friendly! Would definitely stay there again.

name: Micha≈Ç Skowron
text:
The motel is located about 2.5 km from the airport. Every minute or so there's a plane flying almost above your head. Fortunately, the noise isn't that bad when inside the room. The surroundings aren't really interesting.
The room is clean has a big, comfortable bed. It's equipped with an ironing board, iron, flat-screen TV with cable, quite big fridge, mini coffee machine. The bathroom is clean. You get towels, free toiletries and a hair dryer. The room is much better than the overall look and feel of the motel (which is average). The staff is rather nice and helpful. They have a swimming pool but I didn't have a chance to use it.
Breakfast is mediocre. But the add-water-and-stir oatmeal and coffee weren't bad.
Overall impression - a decent place for one or two nights, especially when you travel for several hours and you want sth close to the airport, with a comfortable bed.

text: Very mixed feelings.  Front desk staff was great.  They were out of 'good' pet rooms, offered one in the far back of the hotel.  They were super careful to be sure I was ok with the room.  I was somewhat desperate as I needed some where to stay.  Room was pretty dodgy, as were the neighbors.  The rooms and clientele in front looked fine.  On one hand, I'm happy they are providing housing were it is obviously needed.  On the other, it makes it hard for me to recommend to other travelers.

text:
I was at this location for a wedding. The wedding party was quite fun. Many family members gathered. Drinking, dancing.. General festivities.
The location itself was decent, not exceptional. The bathroom stalls in the men's room, of which there was one, had no lock on the door.
Apparently, it was that same in the ladies room. Beyond that issue, I had no other issues with the venue.

text:

Area was quiet, staff was friendly and helpful and it is clear the new owner cares about the quality of the customer experience.

text: The reservations got "lost" by the hotel, they were rude, demanding, sketchy area. If you like people that are rude or don't understand you go here.

name: BECKY JENSEN
text: Check in was quick and easy. We had to leave a $50 cash deposit which was annoying bc I had to borrow cash from my sister as I didn't have it on hand. The room was decent and upgraded (fresh paint, granite in bathroom, flat screen TV). My sisters room smelled like smoke and a guy came to help us switch us rooms for her. They tried arguing it was a non-smoking room. Whatever room it is, someone smoked in there and they're not sleeping in that. We went to the pool, they were various degrees heated, one looked murky but we avoided it and had a good time. At night I constantly heard people coming up and down the stairs. It was so noisy. Lots of tweakers up and about. The website said breakfast was included but when we got to the lobby it was only coffee. At 11 someone knocked on our door seeing if we were checking out. Moments later at checkout, the front desk radios the guy walking around to physically check our room before giving the deposit back. I just felt like the whole time the hotel was trying to cover their butt and not really caring about the guest. But we checked out fine, got our deposit back and left. Side note: when we called to reserve directly with the hotel they charge $100 more than doing it online.

They didnt appolgise or leave my room.... RUDE!!

name: Tim Newton
text: I would really like to say allot of nice things about this place but I can't think of a whole lot. About the only nice thing was the gal at check in and her hospitality. The room was very big had all the amenities as posted. But there was some kind of stench about it like backed up sewage or something. I was hoping that with time it would dissipate. However, i ended up going to buy some Lysol disinfectant and that only seemed to help for a short while then there smell came back. Luckily i take a sleeping pill so I was able to sleep early. But I was awakened by the sounds of semis in the parking lot at around 2:30. I could not get back to sleep so I stepped out to smoke a cigarette. When I went back inside room I turned the heater on. Once I did that the smoke detector went off. Funny how no one from front desk even came to check on the room. I was finally able to reach the detector and turn it off myself. I decided to start packing but was too tired. I finally got to sleep at around 6:30 am and slept for couple hours. I was afraid I was going to oversleep and be charged an extra night. Thank God I got out. I usually try to avoid places like motel 6 but any motel 6 would be like a palace compared to this place.  I am no snob by any means and I don't have a very big travel account but i would skimp on other things to be able to afford a nicer hotel. I do not recommend this place at all, obviously.

name: Ashley Juarez
text:
We were locked in to our hotel for half an hour and missed out reservations to a restaurant we booked a month in advance to get to. It ruined our night. Even worse when we came back to the hotel , that same door was left unlocked so anyone could enter our hotel and a couple was trapped in elevator. I called the staff and they were completely clueless and no help at all. Worst experience ever in a hotel and this is very dangerous given we were not able to properly exit the hotel. If your building were to ever catch on fire, everyone would be trapped with no way to escape.

Elevator not working -guest service told me to call them back in 5 minutes which is completely unacceptable
Door unable to be opened-my friend called the guest service and he had a horrible attitude. After telling him that no-one is able to open the door from the outside or inside he responded snidely with : its a matter of turning the knob.
resp:
Hello Ashley,
I am very sorry you experienced this inconvenience. We had an issue with the bolt on the lock, and I completely understand your concern. I cannot find your name as a guest, but please reach out to us direct. I would like to apologize personally.
Thank you,
Charlena

name: Israel Carberry
text: I come to SD once a year for work, and this is my go-to place to stay.  Completely self-serve, but you can request just about anything you need.  Only con is their body wash; I bring my own soap.
resp: Thanks for leaving feedback, we are so glad you enjoy your stays with us! We look forward to your next visit to San Diego.

name: Mitch Collins
text: A unique place in the heart of the Gas Lamp district. Cool rooms, great value, nice location.
resp:
Hi Mitch,
Thanks for leaving feedback about your stay! We are so glad to hear you enjoyed your stay with us.  We would love to welcome you back to our center of Gaslamp location the next time you are in town!

name: Jonathan
text: Great place to stay right in the heart of down town. The place is very clean felt like home. Only down side is that if your not out late the noise is notice able if your trying to get an early night rest.
resp:
Hi Jonathan,
Thanks fro the review, and for staying with us! We love your comment, "felt like home". I will share this with our staff. We would love to welcome you back in one of our quieter, rear facing rooms! Thanks again!

name: Todd Warren
text: For the money, it is a decent stay. In the heart of the gas lamp district which is nice if you are looking to bar hop. The entrance is kinda hidden, you have to park up the street at a parking garage. it is $15 a day. Our room was clean. We had the studio on the 3rd floor.  be prepared, It is loud! there is a club right next door so there is music going late. bring ear plugs if you have trouble sleeping in that environment. I have a noise machine so I had no problem. Complaints, elevator is obnoxiously loud. the entry way floors are dirty. If you are looking to save a couple hundred of dollars on your stay, it is a good option. I would stay again.
resp:
Hi Todd,
Thanks so much for staying with us and for leaving feedback. We are glad you liked our location in the center of the lively Gaslamp district. With the busy 5th Ave right outside our door, we do get street noise, though we provide ear plugs in all of our rooms. I will share your feedback with our staff. Thanks again for staying, we hope to welcome you back again!

name: Dr. Monkey
text: We stayed the weekend at this quaint studio apt. It is kind of a cross between a hotel and a hostel. There's a modern, clean private bathroom. Kitchenette with microwave, two stovetop burners, sink, and fridge. Location is spot on! Right in the heart of the Gaslamp Quarter. It's right above a Cuban restaurant so we were concerned about possible noise but even though you could hear music in the stairwell and hallway once you're in the room...peace and quiet. Would recommend.
resp: Thanks so much for staying with us and for providing feedback. We are glad you enjoyed our amenities and central location. We would love to welcome you back on your next visit to San Diego!

name: allan balangue
text: There's no parking here. Nest on Fifth told us to use Park it on Market but neglected to tell us to make a reservation for parking. The receptionist basically told us we're on our own.
resp:
Hi Allan,
Thanks for staying with us and for leaving feedback. Since we are in the center of the Gaslamp district, parking can be a little difficult to come by. We try to offer suggestions in the emails we send prior to arrival.
Although I understand you had frustrations finding parking, I hope you found the location of the apartment convenient and enjoyed your stay.
Thanks again for choosing Nest on Fifth!

name: Edward Murphy
text: Nest on Fifth is a quaint, cute little place in the middle of all the action in the Gaslamp district. We stayed in a room for a couple of nights. Fortunately, the building is within walking distance of a bunch of great bars, a CVS, and restaurants. Our room had a kitchenette, which is great for days when we didn't feel like eating out. Some things we didn't like so much were the loud noises from the surrounding bars and the lack of parking. But we appreciate that ear plugs were supplied. There is a parking structure nearby, but it is not free. We did stay here right before Comicon, so parking was difficult to find. Also, keep in mind that the rooms are like studio apartments. We didn't mind this, but just know that you'd be cooking and sleeping in the same room. Overall, I'd recommend Nest on Fifth if you are fairly young and enjoy the San Diego night life.
resp:
Hi Edward,
We appreciate you leaving us a comprehensive review. We are so glad you enjoyed our neighborhood and amenities. We also have 1 bedroom apartments, in the case you want to spread out a little or invite extra guests next time! We would love to welcome you back.
Thanks again for the great review and for choosing Nest on Fifth!

name: Riverapr 21
text: It's smack in the middle. Full kitchen which is a big plus
resp: Thanks for the review and for staying with us Richard. So glad you enjoyed our central location!

name: mahdi shishehgar
text: Great location, great rooms
resp:
Hi Mahdi,
Thanks so much for leaving feedback. We are glad you enjoyed our downtown, 'center of it all' location! We would love to welcome you back someday soon!

name: lalo valdivia
text: Cozy, in the heart of everything, quiet and clean.
resp: Thanks for staying with us! Thanks for letting us know you had a great time!

name: kevin porter
text: Nice hotel

name: John Lambeth
text: Very goodand spacious
resp: Thanks for the feedback John! So glad you enjoyed our spacious 1 bedroom!

name: Manuel Donati
text:
(Translated by Google) The apartments are located right in the heart of the Gaslamp Quarter, right on the 5th th. The apartment is nice big, well kept and clean. Laundry on the floor. It is not at all calm because the nightlife is noisy in front of it (until after 1 am), and behind because of the various air conditioners.

(Original)
Gli appartamenti si trovano proprio nel cuore del Gaslamp Quarter, proprio sulla 5 th. L'appartamento √® bello grande, tenuto bene e pulito. Lavanderia sul piano. Non √® affatto tranquillo in quanto davanti √® rumoroso per via la vita notturna (fino a dopo le 1 am), e dietro per via dei vari condizionatori.
resp: Thanks so much for leaving us feedback! We appreciate you staying with us.

name: kika miss
text:
(Translated by Google) beautiful renovated apartment. a bit noisy, moreover, in full Fifth. Laundry available. Public parking is $ 20 x 24 hours towards the pier and the congress palace. Dull bed linen and towels. Practical code for doors without keys

(Original)
bell'appartamentino rinnovato. un po rumoroso, d'altronde in piena Fifth. Lavanderia disponibile. Parcheggio pubblico da 20$ x 24 ore verso il pier e il palazzo congressi. Biancheria letto e bagno stramorbida. Pratico codice x le porte senza  bisogno di chiavi
resp:
Hello,
Thanks so much for staying with us! We appreciate you leaving feedback.

name: Andrea Di Giorgi
resp: Thanks for the review!

name: Jeff Provost
resp: Thanks so much for a 5 star review!

name: Natashia Copple
resp: Thanks for the great review Natashia!

name: Deb OHara-Slaughter (Deb)
text: I cannot say enough great things about this hotel! If I could rate it 10 stars I would. AMAZING staff from hotel check-in to pool people. Everyone was kind, polite and helpful. Appreciated the food credits we received with our room rental. Room and beds were over the top!!! One if not the best hotels ive ever stayed in. Will definitely go back next time I'm in the area.

name: Anita Brown
text: Dated interiors in the roomy sunny  and very clean bedrooms.  The lifts were old and dirty.  The reception area was the best part and the staff were friendly and helpful.  Location is excellent right by Pier 39.  I was told they are doing a big refurbishment of the hotel in January.

name: Edwin Ragadio
text:
If you're coming to San Francisco and looking to tour Pier 39 and its neighboring locations, this might be a good choice for you to stay. It is a few blocks away from hopping onto the Cable Car which will take you to North Beach/Chinatown area. There are plenty of restaurants nearby, plenty of shopping, and Boudin factory is only a few blocks away. Coffee is provided in every room. I was on the very top floor and having the nice window, I kept them open and enjoyed the cool breeze! Best I think, is their fire pit located in between their property at the main entrance. When the fog rolls in, sit outside and it feels so cozy!!

Until then, Cheers! ~ :p

name: Matt Morio
text: Located in the touristy fisherman's wharf area this hotel is fine.  Clean comfy rooms.  The lovvy is being remodeled and rooms seem to have been recently updated.   Considering prices i give this 5 stars, overall it's a 4 star but a good value for SF fets extra star.

name: Christine B
text: This place is awesome! Great rooms, bar and lounge area in lobby. Great outdoor fire pit lounge areas. Perfect location by all the tourist pier 39 attractions. Close walking distance to Ghirardelli Square and the cable car ticket booth. Only thing that would make it better is a microwave in the room.

name: A A
text: I checked in at 0100 AM, due to a delayed flight. I thought my situation was bad, until an elderly couple rolled in, having escaped wildfires near their home, only to take an Amtrak train that, as it turned out, would go through ANOTHER wildfire area in Colorado. By the time them made it to San Francisco, CA (by plane), they were even more weary than me. Our female receptionist checked us all in with a warm smile, and bottles of free water. Funny how the smallest gesture can mean so much. My double queen (or was it full?) bedroom was clean, and quiet, and conveniently located around Fisherman's Wharf. Breakfast was free for my room package, which I booked on one of those "book now, and we'll tell you the name of your hotel later" sites. I think I paid $137 via Priceline. Comfortable bed, but awkward layout through may hallways, and "catwalks" to get to my hotel, where half was remodelled to be more contemporary, while the other half (apparently) was still traditional in feel. $$ Expensive, so not much (by San Francisco standards). UPDATE:  There are 6 buildings, so if your Room Number is 2601, you will be on the 2nd Floor, Building 6.  Building 1 contains the Gym, while Building 2, 3, 4, 5, and 6 are linked together with a series of long hallways that provide adequate light, although seem like a fair amount of wasted space.  As of 02/14/2019, the renovation is nearly complete, with a completion date of Summer 2019.  The renovation will include large, updated lobby, and concierge (now assigned to a sad table in a sad, temporary lobby), and get this Superb Restaurant, and Dining Experience! As of this review, there is Cafe Express (or some similar sounding name) that is up a small flight of stairs, off of the ground floor.  Outdoor Pool, gated and open between 0800 - 2200, no life guard.  Gym, 24 hours a day.  Nice rooms (minus the shower enclosure, which is Formica.) Some rooms with balconies, and patios.  Many suites are located on the 4th Floor.  Parking is $63, but across the street at the Safeway parking lot, it is $36.  I would recommend Sheraton Fisherman's Wharf Hotel, SF, CA.

name: Pete Horton
text: Older hotel with a couple of quirks, but good service and clean.  Outdoor fireplaces made this a cozy place.

name: lmfaolouise
text: has a pool, a breakfast bar, near the piers especially pier 43 (literally a 5 minute walk), near the tour buses, has great friendly and professional staff, clean, placed in the middle of great buildings where you can buy food and clothing (goodwill, ross, trader joes) and also to take cute photos for instagram!

name: Harris Ryan
text: Great location. Check in and out was a breeze. Just a heads up parking is $59 per night!!!!!

name: Property Manager
text: We spent 10 days here. The staff was always very helpful. I wish that I could remember all of their names, but Stanford was the first to help us and his professionalism clearly set the tone for the stay. We were very impressed!!! Highly recommend this hotel!!! The only recommendation I would make has nothing to do with how the hotel is run. It is for the architects/designers. We feel that the space in the bathroom could have been maximized by carrying the countertop and the lower shelf all the way across instead of using a decorative vanity. Thank you for a great stay!!!

name: Gavin Williams
text:
Convenient location for visiting the seafront attractions. Staff were very friendly and helpful. Can be quite noisy on the ground floor. My room was right next to a busy intersection so there was quite a bit of noise from passing cars and pedestrians. Dining facilities were limited during my stay. There was a lot of renovation going on so perhaps this will improve in the future.
Ultimately it was an adequate place to stay for a few days of sightseeing.

name: Kristen House
text: Stayed for the weekend with my family - had a lovely time, though our room was quite a haul away. We'd asked for adjoining rooms, but got rooms across the hall from each other. No big deal, but ki d of a pain to keep opening and closing doors.

name: michele vitarelli
text: Parking is a whopping 60 bucks. No breakfast included. Otherwise a nice safe hotel located walking distance to the wharf.

name: Brent Vaughan
text: Nice hotel. A little tricky to find the entrance from the street. They were able to check me in early. Friendly, courteous staff

name: Dymphna Mooney
text:
Very polite.  Clean.  The woman in charge of the breakfast restaurant went out of her way to find me something to eat as i was leaving at 530 am to go on a tour to Yosemite.  They don't even open until 630 but she is kind and caring.  All the staff are polite and patient.  The rooms are clean abs modern.  The gorgeous
Fire pits at night are so fun

name: J Snider
text: The staff here was great. The rooms were modern and appeared recently redone. It is located in a fairly touristy area but North Beach and it's great food is a quick walk. One downside is that the rooms can be noisy. I regularly heard my neighbors or the people down in valet four floors below. Most hotels you will get some noise but this was higher than normal.

name: erica doemland
text: Honestly a beautiful hotel with a great location.  Room was by a bus terminal so it was pretty loud all night but the outdoor fire tables were great.

name: Elizabeth B.
text: Great location, seems that the rooms were upgraded recently only they're small and I kept hearing a lot of noise coming from everywhere at least my room it was like that.

name: Lv K
text:
Good hotel but it could be noisy at night.
We stayed at this hotel for two nights. The location is a couple of blocks from Fisherman‚Äôs wharf and is nice and clean.  There are a few things which made me to give three stars.  1) The entrance and the check in area is very narrow and hard to find; 2) The lounge is inside of a bar,  it‚Äôs kind of awkward; 3) The hotel can be very noisy at night.  Our room was located on the corner of Beach and Mason, across street is a parking lot.  There was a car playing loud music with heavy base.  We reported to the hotel, buy they can not do much since the location was not part of their property.  Music played passed midnight.  I stayed at other hotel in the area and never had the same problem.  Even though it‚Äôs not the hotel‚Äôs fault but I think I need to address this.  Maybe staying in the middle section can avoid the problem but this is a very hotel, customer may not be able to ask for the location of the room.

name: Ganesh Prasad Manjunath
text: The best part about this hotel is it's very close to all the attractions of SFO, also 10 min drive to financial district as well. Very close to Golden Gate as well as Muir Wood National forest as well. Rooms were good and neat & serviced every day on point, But we had a very noisy people in the upper floor and i feel the breakfast offered is very expensive with limited options(There are much better options in walkable distance). There are much better options around for stay. I would recommend to search for other options before booking this hotel.

name: john nicholson
text: Great place to park using spot hero.  Have a bathroom in lobby, which is nice before setting out for site seeing.  Had fire pits for warming at night when it gets chily.  A little out of my price range to stay.  Rooms were about $350 not including a parking fee.

name: Mark Mitchell
text: I really like the location and the outdoor fire pits. The place is showing some wear but still it was a nice stay and I was told that they were doing upgrades soon. The pool and outside meeting lounge are always nice. One of the better places to stay and park your vehicle.  Great staff!

name: Jennifer Lopez
text: Have stayed at this hotel twice over the past few years and really like this hotel! Super nice staff and check in/out process was great even though it was a busy holiday weekend. Will definitely stay here again when we need to avoid driving back to the South Bay after a long night.

name: Mark Mitchell
text: I really like the location and the outdoor fire pits. The place is showing some wear but still it was a nice stay and I was told that they were doing upgrades soon. The pool and outside meeting lounge are always nice. One of the better places to stay and park your vehicle.  Great staff!

name: Jennifer Lopez
text: Have stayed at this hotel twice over the past few years and really like this hotel! Super nice staff and check in/out process was great even though it was a busy holiday weekend. Will definitely stay here again when we need to avoid driving back to the South Bay after a long night.

name: Jennifer Hay
text: Very clean, modern and so close to the Warf, if you want to be in the center of the action you could not pick a better spot. It was my first time in san francisco and I felt like everything was at my fingertips though it is surprisingly quiet within. The grounds were pleasant and cozy.

name: Clinton Stark
text: I would have given it 5 stars but the parking was an absurd $70 night. That's just a ripoff. Go across the street or down the street in its $30 night.  The location is excellent. It's directly across the street from fisherman's wharf. Rooms are very nice. I have seen complaints about the bedding but we thought the bed was very comfortable. There is a fair amount of construction/remodel  going on but they're doing it nicely and it doesn't interfere.  The crew is very nice. Tommy at the front desk was excellent.

name: Alexia Lippman
text: I have had my fair share of hotel stays, and this hotel is BY FAR best hotel I have ever stayed in. From the valet, to the front desk, kitchen staff and janitorial - every single customer/guest services member was EXCEPTIONAL. They are personable, thoughtful and very professional. The rooms were very well kept and extraordinarily clean. The rooms are spacious, modern and have comfy beds. It is well worth the few extra bucks to stay in such a phenomenal hotel. I HIGHLY recommend staying here.

name: Jaime Mendoza
text:
AAA has them rated as a 3 diamond... definitely not.
Heads up, PARKING is NOT INCLEDED in your RESERVATION! Had to have the room keys replaced twice because they didn't work. Manager accompanied me the final time to try the keys, and they finally worked. Then the manager looked at me like an idiot..."you need to hold the key like this"
No, really?!
I will never stay here again. I will talk to my AAA representative and express my disappointment.
Aside from that, the location in Fisherman's Wharf was spot on. 5 stars for the city.

name: Kyle Kixmiller
text: The Sheraton is in a great location, walking distance to Fishermen's Wharf, Alcatraz Boat and many restaurants. The hotel was nice, our room was clean and the staff was helpful. You can tell the hotel is older, but they have renovated and most areas look good.  They have gas fireplaces out front and a restaurant if you want to eat there. It probably won't be the nicest hotel you will ever stay at, but you can't beat the location and the price is right.  I would recommend!

name: Scott Case
text:
The gentleman that checked me in (Tommy) was excellent.  Helpful, friendly and very professional.  He took care of me quickly and efficiently even though I had some questions.

Hotel is good, room was surprisingly small.  Two beds in that room was very "cozy" but not in a good way.  Grounds to be well kept, clean.  I wouldn't hesitate to recommend this hotel

name: Ryan Waddell
text: I stayed here for a conference that was being held at another hotel in Union Square. The front desk was very nice getting me checked in. The room was bigger than I expected and very comfortable. Great location, especially for tourists. Easy to catch an Uber to get to Union Square or elsewhere. Would recommend staying here.

name: Anthony Edillo
text: The location is secure and rooms are huge clean quiet and updated. They also have a fitness center and a restaurant. A grocery store is next door. Great location about a block from the Embarcadero. Parking is underground on site with available valet.

name: taltezy29
text: Great hotel and location. Maggie was very nice and sweet and gave us the lowdown of the area. Maggie is a great hotel hostess.

name: Bunnie
text: The location is impeccable. It took us only 4 minutes to walk to pier 39! The hotel itself is clean and beautiful decorated with outdoor lounges and fire pits. Inside the lobby we found a darling cafe and friendly staff. There is paid parking under the hotel or free parking on the street with certain restrictions. We had called to house keeping for a toothbrush kit and it came fairly quickly. The bedding was so warm and comfortable. I took the comforter from the bed and a cup of tea from the in room coffee machine to the couch and was too comfortable to move until our 2 PM late check out. I cant wait for my next excuse to visit the Sheraton Fisherman's Warf Hotel.

name: Franco Amalfi
text: It was a good hotel for what I needed.  A little out of the way from the center of San Francisco, but perfect to do activities in the Pier.

name: Fawny Fawn
text: Hotel staff was friendly. Cleaning maids were extremely friendly and helpful. Hotel looks clean and beds were comfy. With the exception of parking cost at $62 a night (which includes in and out privileges) it beats roaming around trying to find a spot to park your vehicle.

name: Troy Kelly
text:
Response to Response: What a non-reply! My stay should have fallen short of YOUR expectations. What you are saying is that you are okay with your rooms being disgusting and filthy.
I hope this review serves as a warning - this hotel considers filthy rooms to be acceptable. Do not stay here.
Original Review: Rude, unhelpful and unapologetic front desk staff.
Unengaged managers who couldn't care less about issues guests raise.
Unclean rooms with broken lights, filthy A/C filters and poorly / improperly made beds.
Find somewhere else, Sheraton might have been a good brand years ago - it's not worth your money or time any more.

name: Steve T
text: Little bit of construction, but great location. The staff here is great and friendly. This is close to everything on the waterfront.

name: Skylar Dunning
text:
Room recently renovated. Good location. We walked to North Beach for dinner most nights which was better than eating in the wharf. Enjoyed our stay.

Probably not worth the price, but we always felt self walking around the hotel area and had no huge complaints like others had.

Have to rent a mini fridge if you want one, which is pretty crazy for a $300 night hotel. We just used ice machine ice to keep things cold in the sink. Also, very expensive wifi if you want it in the room. Available in lobby for free.

name: Atul kumar Sinha
text: Nice hotel , well located near pier. All facilities available here.

name: Hari Krishna Gudladona
text: Very nice hotel in the downtown area very near to fishermans warf. Could just walk to the prime points like sea gulls etc They have a fireplace outside the hotel which we liked

name: Brian Weaver
text: Concierge was less than helpful. When I told her I had a delivery for a room, she called the room number and handed me the phone with a look like she stepped in something. Hopefully they treat their guests better.

name: Luke Pedersen
text:
The room was a real bargain for the location. Nice and modern. But...for some reason or room was at street level right inside the lobby of the second building. Thankfully we were exhausted,  but we heard people yelling on the street and entering the hotel all night. If we weren't so tired and feel right asleep on an amazingly comfortable bed, this would have been annoying as hell.

Also, no water bottle for your morning coffee... really? That's pretty cheap.

Anyway, small details to overlook for a clean room in a great location.

name: Eric Young
text: Was pleasantly surprised by how great this location is and how nice the rooms are. Quiet at night, comfortable beds and great staff. Would be nice if they improved on the TV channels.  But this is a great spot to get to various areas of San Francisco.

name: Albert Lucas
text: A short walk ( less than a block) to Pier 39 and all of the surrounding activities. Friendly staff that gave suggestions about places to visit and local spots the tourists crowd would not find. Grocery and shopping within a block. Room was small yet adequate. The room withstood my wife's inspection, and we're satisfied with the cleaning service when we requested our room cleaned.

name: Cynthia Preciado
text: Though the parking might be terrible the attraction is amazing. Ate clam chowder, it was thick and creamy with chunks of the heavenly food food. Saw and met many interesting people along the way. Went to the arcade that was near and it was a great time spending it with the family.

name: Albert van Lingen
text: Very nice hotel. Walking distance from Pier 39. We had a great room and an awesome experience. Super friendly staff. Would definitely stay here again. Only down side is the parking but that's San Francisco for you. At least the staff gave me some advice for cheaper parking across the street at safway.

name: Dennis Cardoso
text: The staff are very friendly and attentive.  The property is a bit dated and shows the wear and tear.  Rooms are decent size, but bathroom was very small.  They apply a lot of fragrance in common areas, but I also found landing at elevator bank malodorous.  Pool and patio area is highlight of the property.  Good location for visiting city's top tourist attractions.

name: jbetha825
text: Nice hotel, conveniently located within walking distance to everything. The concierge was a great help. However,  for the price we paid, I expected to at least have a microwave and fridge in the room and there wasn't a real bar, but a bar area so no ambiance.

name: Rachel Garza
text: The memory of the hotel will be memorable. The decor was quite 70s. And reminded me of the movie Catch me if you can. I expected to see a pilot and some pan am Stewart's it was great. They have nice fireplace settings and a great continental breakfast. I recommend it.

name: Taylor Ramos
text: This hotel has quite a learning opportunity when it comes to the treatment of service animals versus pets. They forced us to sign a document which was an agreement to keep a service animal (with all possible paperwork available regarding the dog's credentials) out of public eating and drinking spaces, regardless of the dog's need to assist my guest in these areas. When asked if we could line-out the area of the animal agreement regarding access to public eating areas the manager's response was, "either you sign this agreement as-is, or I will cancel your reservation." This hotel does not discern between pets and service animals and literally required that we not have access to public areas with a service animal.

name: Andrew Choi
text:
An old Sheraton so don't expect a nice Sheraton.

They only have up to two doubles.
Parking is +/- $60!!! That's where they get you.

Although it does offer a good location in front of pier 39 and it is next to some supermarkets.

Internet is only free in the lobby not in the rooms.

The house keeping lady opened our door after one quick knock to ask me what time I'm leaving at 930AM! Thank god I was awake and I was dressed! Ridiculous, what kind of hotel does this? Keep your doors all locked.

name: Moises Castellanos
text:
Is really clean
But I give them a 3 stars because
they charged $56 for parking on their facility
Even though I was paying $262 a night
& not been so close to the water
customer service was good they do a good job
There is other hotels that have a prize range under $150  night
There is other facilities that charged less then $35
For parking
I hope it helps if anyone decided to stay here
God bless you all

name: Chris Gaun
text: Previously labeled this as a three star solid hotel in SF. They remodeled recently and it is much nicer than it was a year ago.

name: Micah Gaudio
text: Older Sheraton hotel located a few blocks and short walk to the wharf or the pier. Overnight self parking is $56 per night. This is not a View Hotel, there are only four stories. Tommy at the front desk was great. This may be a 4-star hotel from the outside and lobby but our room was definitely not a four-star.

name: Brokk margetts
text: What a great trip. We had a really nice room at the Sheraton. The bellhop guys are probable the best I have ever met. Front desk was not bad. It is a really busy hotel so be prepared.

name: James Edwards
text: Stayed 3nights lovely stay and good location nr fisherman's wharf. Rooms where wonderful and beds were very comfortable. Would not hesitate  to come back.

name: Kevin Mulder
text: The Sheraton is a nice hotel & is walking distance to Fishermans Wharf. The room was clean & spacious. The only two issues I had were having to pay $15 a day for Internet & $56 a day for parking. Internet was free in the lobby but who wants to spend time doing that!?! Overall, it's definitely worth it for the location.

name: David Desouza
text: The room is clean, modern, and spacious. Great outdoors heated pool, my kids loved it even on a cool evening with some light rain. Reception was quick and very pleasant. Excellent stay, reasonably priced except for the parking (to be expected in this area). Clise walk to Pier 39 and the surrounding Fisherman's Wharf area.  Would definitely stay here again.

name: ky spit
text: Nice pleasant hotel in prime area in San Francisco. Good location relative to Fishermans Wharf. Amenities are nice. Kinda noisy outside since it is by a transit maintenance station. Would stay here again. No resort fees which is a plus!

name: Sumana Barua
text: Good location but no comparison with any other Sheratons where we stayed. Room was small, maintenance and upkeep are question marks. There was no one at the reception when we arrived, it was past midnight though. We waited a bit and then  someone turned up. Sheraton at Niagara-on-the-Lake is just awesome.

name: Jim Hendrix
text: The location is great, just off fisherman's wharf.  The staff is friendly and efficient but the decor is dated.  The room and premises were very clean.  They also let me check in at noon.  A definite plus.

name: Jessie Casey
text: While this place might be up to date on its trendy color themes & outside appeal, I wouldn't stay here again if you paid me. The room smelled so badly like moth balls it will give you a headache. After opening windows & blasting the fan, it wouldn't go away. Bedding, poor and over used, the springs pop and poke.The front desk & guest services answered on the third try. Poor customer service. While this post may seem drastic, I am very realistic, and least of all fussy. I cannot believe the cost vs the lack of any quality.

name: ky spit
text: Nice pleasant hotel in prime area in San Francisco. Good location relative to Fishermans Wharf. Amenities are nice. Kinda noisy outside since it is by a transit maintenance station. Would stay here again. No resort fees which is a plus!

name: Daniel Moody
text:
Great location, great staff.

The location couldn't be better for the things I like to do around the city.

I called down looking for some shaving cream because I know Sheraton stocks that for some rooms and they sent me up a bag with several little tubes. Great service.

name: Paul Kang
text:
Clean hotel and friendly staff for the most part. I just wish they would have handled my check-in a little quicker after I stood in the Gold/Platinum line for almost 5 minutes while others were being helped. No worries though. I would recommend to anybody wanting to stay in the Fisherman‚Äôs Wharf area.

Plus, the SPG lounge offers free drinks and snacks that would be otherwise expensive at a local convenience store.

name: Neil Silverman
text: Rooms are fine. Staff friendly.  But nothing out of the ordinary overall.  Also hit you with you with a  twenty dollar a day destination fee.

name: Dana Davidson
text: Nice rooms, great location, friendly staff.

name: The Traveler
text: Really nice experience. Location is fantastic if you're looking to be near the pier. The thing that stopped me from giving 5 stars was that you can't get fresh air into your room, at least from the fourth floor, and the water pressure in the shower was very weak. That said, I would stay here again.

name: Curt Faust
text: Nice hotel in a great location.  Only issue is noise from the road. If you're sensitive to that, go for a room in the interior of the hotel.

name: Rob Birse
text:
Better than expected.

The decor in the corridors shows its age and reflects the style of the 1980's but the rooms are decent. However the bathroom in my room was small.

The location is very tourist oriented so think twice if you plan to be visit the downtown area.

name: john lopez
text:
I‚Äôve stayed here multiple times . It‚Äôs a good place to stay . I‚Äôve taken my children with me on a few occasions and it is very kids friendly . It‚Äôs located right near many restaurants and a CVS if have a quick shopping need . They provide great customer and Bell service. The room is always clean and they provide robes for you to use . There is a pool a restaurant. There is a small little cafe in the lobby near the check in desk .
There are 3 elevators so your not waiting. A room key card is required to go up past the 1st floor .
There is parking in basement, but there is a separate charge for parking .
Stay here and you can walk easily to the piers of San Francisco easily .
I have stayed here many times and never had a bad experience.

name: Sarah L
text: Very nice. No fridge or microwave in the room, no free breakfast, $52/day parking, but you have until 4pm to leave your parking space after checkout. Very convenient location & there is a Safeway & a Trader Joe's within walking distance.

name: Robert Woblesky
text: Great hotel and great location. Very close to Fisherman's Wharf and North Beach. To top it all off, Mayra, the associate that checked us in, sent up a beautiful fruit basket on the house to celebrate my Wife's birthday! Great service, will return soon!

name: Jarvin Bayona
text: The corner rooms are great. But the restrooms are tiny! Service is goood!

name: yousef alhuzami
text: Good location, the rooms were less than what was expected, I didn't like the breakfast there

name: Erica Long
text: The location was ideal for sightseeing around San Francisco. The room was really nice and the hotel appeared to have been updated recently. The parking seemed cheaper than other hotels but was the same price after taxes.

name: Ar Cr
text: Is very convenient everything is in walking distance. Love it almost 15 years booking this hotel every year no free breakfast üôÅ

name: Ashley Fry
text: Hotel was in a nice location to walk down to the warf. They're in the process of renovating but still feels a bit old. Everything was clean, which was nice. Buffet breakfast was $27/pp, which is pretty steep.

name: Lisa G
text: Great hotel, comfy rooms and inviting sheets on the beds. Self parking is easy, and service was friendly.. recommend for sure!

name: Mark Atkinson
text:
This is a property very near the Wharf as is obvious. Rooms are nice.

Recommended if pricing is good.

name: Andrew Stevens
text: Very convenient location for Fishermans Wharf and with Safeway and a Trader Joe's across the street it's easy to find lots of inexpensive and fresh food.

name: james Brown
text: Good location, friendly staff, nice room, good quality bed linen, enjoyed my stay

name: Laurie Carty
text: Wifi awful and rooms small but comfortable & great staff

name: Camiesha Andrews
text: Perfect location, Nice place to visit.You can order room service,swim, work out with internet access,valet parking,car rentals and the customer service is wonderful!

name: Eva Veronica Willis
text: GREAT LOCATION, COZY ROOMS WITH A MODERN FLARE

name: Mr Matthew. Russell
text: Location good. No fridge in room. Buffet breakfast was nothing special. Pool was good. Nice views of Alcatraz, Golden Gate and city from roof top.

name: The Dream
text: Great location,excellent stuff doormen,bellmen and front desk, thank you i recommend this hotel located at the fisherman's wharf of San Francisco.

name: Ben Gonzales
text: Nice location and a great workout area. Hotel seems to be recently renovated and had a nice Gold area with continental breakfast and coffee. Close to restaurants and grocery store.

name: Robert Moore
text: Hotel itself well kept and great location. Staff was friendly and accommodating. Would definitely stay again.

name: Eric J.
text: Not too impressed... This Sheraton quality is lower then other same priced hotel ... Breakfast was over priced and definitely could be better. Bathroom is really small... Not sure if I will come back. I'm not saying that this hotel is bad but it doesn't reach other same priced hotels.

name: Angela Lau
text: I was thankful for being able to check in early and reception staff were helpful and friendly.  Location is also great if you want to take the ferry to Sausalito/Tiburon as its very close to Pier 41 which is very close to the very popular Pier 39.  So in terms of mega popular touristic location this is it! I wouldn't want to be in this area the whole time though as its very popular with families! The hotel has really great fireplaces outside but unfortunately it is not sufficiently manned so there are numerous homeless people taking up space while hotel guests end up sharing! Then the bar closes at 11pm! Yup this is definitely a family-hotel!

name: Philip Etienne
text: my favorite place to stay in SF - well situated away from heavy business area, but close enough to walk to financial district and china town - also near wharf and stadium so that you never need to uber - the vibe is upbeat and conducive to relax when needed

name: Dan Kaplan
text: Great location, hotel was just a couple blocks from the Wharf. Room was decent sized and were able to accommodate a dog. 24 hour fitness center was basic and the pool was decent. Not a bad value.

name: Jennifer Hay
text: Very clean, modern and so close to the Warf, if you want to be in the center of the action you could not pick a better spot. It was my first time in san francisco and I felt like everything was at my fingertips though it is surprisingly quiet within. The grounds were pleasant and cozy.

name: Richard Gibson
text: The location of this hotel is ideal for a tourist visiting San Francisco. Walking distance from F line, and the pier, and lots of food and tourist attractions (such as the city bus, etc.) The inside of the room was very clean and the bed was extremely comfortable, I slept like a baby. The one draw back is that the you can hear guests above you walking pretty easily so if you trying to sleep in, and the guests above you are early risers, you may find yourself woken by footsteps.

name: Abhinav Shroff
text: Helpful staff and awesome location....

name: Radek Kobylka
text: Interesting decor in the hallways, friendly staff and large rooms. Some rooms have a limited view but the location of the hotel is superb. Great access to the wharf, ocean and all the seafood restaurants you could want.

name: Jarvin Bayona
text: The corner rooms are great. But the restrooms are tiny! Service is goood!

name: Daniel R
text: My wife surprised me on a surprise birthday trip to fisherman's wharf sharaton.we got an early check in and Rosie at the bonvoy elite line was so sweet and helpful and she comped us free parking for my birthday.when we got to the room it was nice and had a balcony overlooking the hotel.a knock on the door and in comes a bottle of red wine and a ice bucket with a bottle of prosecco on ice a cheese sampler and strawberries dipped in chocolate omg!!!thank you marilou B.and cindy Wei kept the room clean and was on our schedule so when we came back to the room it was clean and left us notes everyday. Hotel was very  nice and pool was good and it's so close to the wharf. Thank you Sheraton  for the great birthday u made it very special for me.

name: Malaika Kanavalli
text: Stayed for only one night. Good location walking distance to restaurants and Fisherman's Wharf.  No free continental breakfast or free WiFi in your hotel room only available in the lounge. Room was very clean and bed was extremely comfortable so you will definitely have a good night's sleep.  Starbucks coffee in the room was delicious.

name: Nikki Than
text: Conveniently located in Fisherman's Wharf with a 5 minute walk to Pier 39. Customer service was great from front desk, bellman, and cleaning staff. The rooms we got were updated, clean, and modern don't be alarmed by their exterior it's updated! Decent size room for a double queen bed. -Rooms:clean, roomy, no mini fridge -parking with in and out $62 (24 hours). Underground garage parking. If you decide to park in the street read the signs carefully!! They have a seating area outside with firepits to hang out.

name: David Luu
text: Really nice hotel.  Stayed with family in a double bed room was nice and clean.  I give it a 3.5 star rating.

name: Kevin Mullett
text: I really like this hotel, it is a great location central to fisherman's wharf.  The only problem is the bathrooms are too small. I am a big guy but I had to go downstairs to use the bathroom in the lobby!! It is terribly small. Other than that the hotel is great

name: Jaime Schaffer
text: Book here for the location, but don't expect a whole lot extra for your money.  Take the Bart in if you can. Expensive parking and drinks, but you can bring your own alcohol and hang out by the great fire pits out front.  Friendly and helpful staff, clean room, but nothing special.  Don't plan on hanging in the room.  Very loud at night, we were right over the corner of North Point and Mason and it was loud, but so was the A/C unit.

name: Ken Hamilton
text: Nice stay. Definately not a downtown hotel but great value for cost. Safeway next door, fabulous little fitness area. Poolside deck chairs and very well located. Walk to Fort Mason (3 miles) fisherman's wharf, one block, Embarcadero and transit, one block, trolleys five blocks and piers....and fun stuff within a mile.

name: Ryan OLeary
text: It's an ok hotel. Its expensive simply because it's in fishermans wharf and they can. The rooms are dated and the hotel in general needs an overhaul. Probably would find another hotel next time I'm in the area.

name: Mike Adamson
text: Great place to stay for Fishermen's Warf.  It is $$$ but worth it. Staff are excellent. Like they say "you get what you pay for". Excellent stay.

name: Dana Taylor
text:
Clean and polite staff.
Couples and family friendly.

name: Liliana Santos-Gonzalez
text: Beds are super nice they were doing a lot of remodeling but still a nice stay!

name: Zaid
text: Beautiful hotel, located right next to a touristie area and next to safe way and trader Joe's. It is nice if you want to buy a quick thing for your day and it is literally across the street

name: Jahongir Holbaev
text:
Great hotel. Awesome location for spending vacation. I love fireplace outside, where you can sit and enjoy glass of wine. Good
breakfast and great service. Will come back again.

name: INDEPENDENT BARTENDER
text: This place is Elegant and Modern. Didn't like that they charged a $200 deposit. Sucks that it is right next to a bus yard (but they do give you ear plugs). Its is conveniently located. Walking distance to Fishsermans Wharf. The main thing I didn't like was that the room had no ventilation what so ever. Everything you did in the bathroom would linger into the room. It is a must to open up the windows out to the street. I loved the free ammenities tooth brushes, tooth paste, slippers, robes etc. Didn't like that if we wanted to have a fridge or microwave we had to pay extra. The room was the cleanest I've been in so far. Not one hair in the bathroom before we used it. Had to pay for parking but considering it being San Francisco it was not bad especially since our parking was validated till 4pm the next day after checkout

name: Geof Greenway
text: Pretends to be a really nice hotel, but the facade runs thin. Bathrooms are so small you can barely turn around, drains consistently drain very slowly, and it just isn't really that great. Entryway fire tables and seating areas and the lobby Cafe look very inviting.

name: Kym Dwyer
text: It would have been a nice room if we had been placed further up. Ground floor looking out onto seating/bar area. Blinds closed the entire time. Also very noisy at night with guard booth attendants shouting, car doors slamming, engines revving, general noise from out side people.

name: Daniel R

Hotel was very  nice and pool was good and it's so close to the wharf. Thank you Sheraton  for the great birthday u made it very special for me.

text: Bedding was good quality as I have come to expect from the Sheraton.  The room was dated but mostly maintained.  Avoid staying on the street level near the fitness center it was very noisy both with street noise and hallway noise.  I struggle between 2 & 3 Star decision because there were clear lazy housekeeping issues I would not expect from a quality hotel.  Towels that should not be in guest circulation any longer, hair in sink, dirty smudges on wall, dried toothpaste on wall.
