name: Erik Lemons
text: I went to the Motel 6 after leaving the Country Inn a half mile away.  The Country Inn had mold in the tub, the phone didn't work, and other issues with the room.  They didn't change my room so I left. I went to Motel 6 and something must have been going on in the area because that was the only hotel available in Long Island City.  The only people there were others who couldn't find rooms at other hotels.  When I checked in,  I told the gentleman behind the desk of my experience at The Country Inn, and he laughed and said "The phone here probably won't work either ". I thought he was joking until I got to the room and there was no closet, no ironing board or iron, the phone didn't work,  amongst other things.  I went to the front desk and the guy said that he'd make a note of it and if have to talk to the manager in the morning.  The manager the next day didn't come in until noon and still didn't care and did nothing about the issue.  I'd never stay there again and would recommend others not to go.  Also it was the midst expensive Motel 6 ive ever stayed at.  Over $200 for a terrible room.

text: Great soup. Old school, I mean real old school sandwiches.  Where else can you get a limburger cheese sandwich? Or a liverwurst sandwich.   Did I mention absolutely delicious soup.  If you love an old building with some charm this should be on your list.  Again did I say the soup is incredible.

name: Frank Coriddi
text: Excellent homemade soup and sandwiches. The food was delicious and hot, the way it is supposed to be served, and the beer was nice and cold. I always like trying soups when I eat out. I had the yellow split soup and my wife had the garbage plate soup, both were served nice and hot and were very good. My wife also enjoyed her buffalo chicken wing wrap, as I did a turkey reuben on rye. Again, both sandwiches were served nice and hot. We have lived south of Lima for many years and wish we had tried the American Hotel sooner. We'll definitely be back.

name: Hugo Stackel
text:
I was told by a friend that this place is very good; he was absolutely right too! Our group decided to order the soups of the day- and there were a half dozen tempting offerings. I was torn between the Pork and Barley or the Cheeseburger Chowder. I ended up ordering the Cheeseburger Chowder and was very pleased with my selection. My only regret is that I ordered a cup rather than a bowl, because it was simply excellent! My companions opted for the French Onion Soup and they both raved about it. To go with our soups, we all ordered sandwiches- I had the Grilled Cheese, they had Reubens. Again, all of us agreed that our sandwiches were very tasty! I was very happy with the quality of the food, it was better than average. I feel the portions were generous too, as well as everything seemed very fresh and delicious.

Beyond the very satisfying meals, we all enjoyed the ambiance of this establishment. When you reach the front door, you immediately take note of a small plaque denoting that the place goes back to 1861, as a history buff I really found this interesting. It's clear that the building has been around a LONG time, it has the charm. It is a well maintained looking place and oozes charm and warmth. It was interesting to read that the same family has owned and operated the place for a century and it is also a functioning hotel! Pretty cool!

The service was good, our server was friendly and attentive, and the prices were reasonable and fair. So, overall, in every aspect...The American Hotel left us pleased with our decision to check it out. We left saying that we would return! This place would make most people happy in my opinion!

text: I stayed here a week and found it to be a lovely hotel.  I first had a very nice room at the front and then moved to a suite at the back, both on the top floor, which I think was the sixth or seventh.  I then, unfortunately, renewed via the internet and opted for a slightly cheaper room on the floor below, the mouse visitor having apparently left - true and not being snide, it was very small and the rooms were very clean - I put down food for it but then it disappeared.  There was some problem with the room change and I was asked to leave, perhaps because they found out about the mice feeding, and there were no rooms available on subsequent visits. name: Michelle Johnson
text: The design, layout and location of the hotel are great. You can take a nice stroll to Madison Square Park or the Empire State building. I love the TV service and mini fridge and the suite setup I had. However, I can only see more negatives about this hotel than I can see positive. I want to honestly say the hotel isn't worth what I paid for. It has cheap quality for expensive prices. I was already concerned when the receptionist looked like he didn't know what he was doing every time I walked through the lobby. I was right to be concerned because they put me in the wrong room. I will applaud the fast speed of resolving that issue, however; there were only two outlets in the room, both at very awkward and inconvenient locations. At one point the outlet fried my charger, forcing me to buy a new one after the receptionist looked clueless about my complaint. The toilet doesn't flush all the way, you'll have to flush it twice to get even a small sheet of tissue down. That was a big turn off for me. They deducted an extra $25 as a deposit in case there was any damages in the room after I left, this would be returned to my card if no damages were made. I can definitely understand this, but it was not mentioned to me at all upon booking my room which was very upsetting. When I first initially reserved the room, I was informed my grand total would be $380, but then the price raised to $410, and then it raised to $477. I don't understand why because I booked the room for what it was worth at $380 but ended up paying $477, such a total ripoff. I saw reviews and was warned by a random user to book somewhere else. But knowing we as humans have different tastes, I booked it anyway to give it a chance. But I'm very bitter about my stay overall and will not suggest this place to anyone. I wish I took the advice to book somewhere else.

text: The 5 star rating is for the cabin my daughter and her family occupied which was fully furnished, had modern kitchen and bath and in a good location. My wife and I were in a barebones building that was due for floor and shower stall replacement. In fairness, these are old buildings that are probably updated when funds are available.  If you are a tent camper, accustomed to leaking tents and damp ground conditions our accommodation would be considered a "glamping" experience. And, for $585 for 7 nights this cabin is a bargain. Access to a beautiful lake with swimming, boating and fishing at your doorstep is a wonderful experience. Office and maintenance staff are wonderful people who respond to your needs.  Be aware that some cabins are accessed from upper road parking down pretty steep lawns.  Some renters were using their trucks and SUVs with AWD and 4WD to drive down grass slopes to unload and load their vehicles. I couldn't do this with my vehicle and had to make many trips back and forth to it arriving and departing. OK if your capable but consider cabin 155 with roadside parking if you're not.

name: Mr Azlan the Landlord
text:
Unhelpful reception. They are not empowered to do anything; not even pass on defect info to maintenance. They won‚Äôt even accept deliveries (courier) on behalf of guests, so I had to camp out at reception all day for UPS to arrive. The rooms are tiny, 15 ft by 15 ft at most and the ensuite toilet was an afterthought. Check in time is 1600 hrs; if you arrive early, as we did, we had to leave and come back after 1600 hrs. They charge USD7 for every piece of luggage stored in their luggage room.  A rip off, if you ask me; but we didn‚Äôt have a choice. Opportunist capitalists!

On the plus side, at USD29/night the rate is considered the cheapest in NYC; the fridge is large and they supply towels. The only useful thing reception did for us was to give us two sets of keys.

Pity we don‚Äôt have much of a choice.

text: Older building - a safe, clean place to stay near the airport. There are not very many amenities, but everyone is very nice and will help with whatever they can. The tavern has a very small menu but staff is lovely and very accommodating! Fries are awesome. More outlets in the room would be great.

name: Mark Reed
text: We recently had an appreciation banquet for our pastor. In time past, the service was deserving of a 5 star and the reason we decided to have the event there. We were told that the space-room would be ready upon our arrival at 12 as the event started at 4pm. We arrived at 1pm to a dirty banquet hall. It was not cleaned from the event the night before. We assisted with the clean up and set up of the room to ensure it was ready by 4pm. Unfortunately with all our effort, the room was not ready at 4. Dinner was set to be served at 5:30pm. Prior to dinner we discover that most of the glassware was dirty, some with lipstick. We ran out of food and had to find someone to refill it as servers was not available. We spoke with the owner afterwards. He was extremely rude and offered no resolution. We will not be returning and would not recommend this venue.

name: Zowwee Luciano
text: There were no towels or toilet paper in the room. I was handed towels only and a roll of toilet paper. No shampoo or tissues or garbage bags. The light in the bathroom flickered. The halls smelled of weed and sewage. People stood outside by where the cars parked, smoking. The pool was open but not the hot tub. The temperature fluctuated in the main areas constantly. When we went to check out, there was no one at the desk, only a note that they would be back soon with an emergency number, so we waited 10 minutes for someone to come back. The most positive thing was the cleaning staff who was very friendly.

name: Shane O'Malley
text: This place is so bad, they probably won't stay open much longer. No towels, soap or shampoo were in the rooms on arrival. Very few of the side doors worked to let you in. The bar has no drafts. Housekeeping came by the room and woke me up at 7am to see if I was checking out (had 2 more nights remaining). The place is run down, the "best" smelling rooms are musty. Would recommend staying anywhere but here.

name: Jenny Perez
text: It's really worth a 1/2 star but that's not an option.  There are no real amenities.  The room was semi-clean and beds were made however there was a little mold in my bathroom. There were no towels in our bathroom, we had to request them.  The ice machine closest to my room was out of service and looked dirty.  The pool was shut down by the health department.  The fitness room DOES NOT LOOK LIKE THOSE PICTURES!! The owner has a lot of work to do and he should get on it!!!!

name: OA Dorsey
text:
This hotel is one of the worse hotels ever in Rochester, NY. I was here for an event on Saturday,  and there was absolutely no staff provided for the function, the room was not even set up, the food was HORRIBLE, and the sound system wad a total disaster.  I have worked I banqueting before and this hotel does not have what it takes to host events. The manager was very unprofessional and rude,  and so was the events coordinator....she was so rude and had no professional decorum.  She walked around the room I flip flops serving the guest the worst lemonade EVER. Then after we are, there was no one to take our plates. They stayed on the function until the event ended.....WHO DOES THAT!

This hotel has change management more times than I care to remember.  I would not consider this place to host any event ever again. The only person who is even worth mentioning is Michael (recently hired.) who was so nice and assisted us in whatever we needed(he was not even suppose to be there.) I was so disappointed at the service we received,  I would never think of coming back to this hotel for any function even a stay if I could help it.

Spider webs in the room by the lights. Parking lot full of garbage and the outside area by doors full of cigarette butts and garbage. They don‚Äôt deep clean in-between guests is the first thing that comes to mind as a reason for that. I don‚Äôt know. For a more expensive room in the area, I really expected more. We booked our room when they were a Marriott.  When we got there, they told us we were getting a king bed with a pullout couch.  We booked two queens for me, my wife and daughter and we had just driven 6 hours.  They first tried to tell us that we booked a single (occupant) but our reservation clearly showed it was for 3.  The woman was making all kinds of BS excuses and lies.  The lobby stunk of chlorine and there was a paper sign stating the pool was out of service.
When we got to the room, it was just ok but kinda felt cheap.  The towels were absolutely horrible and were so rough they felt like brillo.  Would never go there again.  BE ADVISED!

name: Chris S
text: The day before I was staying at the hotel I recieved a phone call saying due to renovations there will be no continental breakfast and the pool will not be open. They took $15 off the stay. I was ok with that. Upon check in(3pm), I tried to find the entrance. The one that looked like it had tarps and dust all over. It looked like an abandoned building. I called to confirm the entrance and was told it was. There was plastic and dust everywhere in the "lobby". I brushed it off since they gave me a discount.  I got to the room and the key didn't work. The couple next door were having the same problem. Luckily the second key worked so I didn't have to go bacl to the front desk. I wanted to take a nap but it was still light out. When I went to close the curtains, I noticed they were very dirty. It was like someone with oil on there hands closed them. After my nap I wanted to watch t.v. but the satellite was down... I was quite disappointed but at least the wifi worked. The next morning when I went to shower I noticed quite a but of black mold on the ceiling and wallpaper in the shower. It made me feel dirtier than before I showered. I went to make coffee and of course remnants of the previous guests were still in the coffee maker. What a surprise. I should have taken the free cancelation and booked somewhere else...

name: Patrick Mullins
text: Too many positive vocabulary words to use regarding this hotel. Firstly, what a gorgeous neighborhood! Old New York, clear as day! Gorgeous views of the Brooklyn Bridge! Large pedestrian-friendly location with rental bikes and a pick-up location for various tours. Staff is FIVE STAR. The manager was voraciously accommodating and made sure we had everything we needed while seeming genuinely happy to be at work. And the attitude showed throughout the establishment. It was my mom's first time to New York and it couldn't have been more perfect! Thank you so much for making this an unforgettable trip!

name: Rajsri Bipat
text: This hotel is great because of the location and convenience of being in downtown Manhattan. It's an old building, with old elevators. Could use some updating. The rooms are nice enough but not nice enough for the $$ that they charge per night. Breakfast was basically a cold breakfast, except for the "eggs" which I think were badly reconstituted powdered eggs. I've stayed in hotels that cost way less, but have infinitely better breakfasts.

name: Jo Hawke
text: Although we've been to the City many times over the years, July 2015 was our first time staying at this hotel or in Seaport. Our room was clean, and most of the staff was very nice (one of the breakfast ladies got an attitude when we asked for cream cheese for the bagels...they were out). The neighborhood was nice, a lot more quiet compared to uptown where we usually stay, especially at night. The Fulton St station we needed was down, unfortunately, though, so we ended up having to walk to City Hall every time: a brisk 12-15 minutes. It was pretty inconvenient, but we got a lot of exercise. :) The parking rates listed on their website were not updated, so be sure to clarify this before you book.

name: Dale Campbell
text: Great hotel. However the room I paid for was not avaiable when I checked in and they tried to cover it up by giving me an upgrade. The room I was upgraded to was smaller than I needed for the first night. Otherwise it was an awesome experience.

name: Abraham Taub
text: This is not a 5 star hotel, but it sure is a nice and cozy place to stay in Downtown, NY. The room was clean and spacious, the clerk at the front desk was extraordinarily nice, and the staff was very helpful.

name: Dave Chapman
text: Quaint, classic decorations make the room enjoyable. The location makes the stay enjoyable.

name: Kyle Bubp
text: Great location, helpful staff, and reasonable rates. I would stay here again for sure!

name: Gilles
text: Very nice decoration in the lobby. Rooms are nice too.

name: Alexander Bartash
text: Quiet place by NY standards. There is also a gym inside.

name: Erika Devash
text: It was in a good location but the hotel needs to be updated.

name: David Smith
text: I loved this hotel great location

name: Yura Kim
text: This is a cute hotel with complimentary breakfast!

name: Laifj Jsad
text:
(Translated by Google) Hotel location is good, just under the high speed place. The nearby environment is very quiet, parking and unloading luggage are very convenient. There is a paid parking lot across the street. South St seaport is just a few blocks away. The only downside is that it is a long way to get to the nearest Fulton subway station, which takes about ten minutes. This is not particularly good. It can only be said that if you want to live next to the subway, this is not your choice. Our room is around the corner,

name: Ratih D. L. Martial
text:
Insist my husband to drive here just to found out the affordable "budget" rate listed is outdated! While the staff is friendly, she explained "its" for winter rate thus we decided to walk out and stay somewhere else with similar rate and consistent reviews.

In case you saw and tempted with interesting "budget" rate for this place?! Please don't hesitate to call and confirm the rate OR just book online to secure a better rate.

name: A'Siyah Ad-Deen Islam
text: It was last minute and the price I was looking to pay. By sister has stayed here so I called and got a, king size bed in a nice comfy room. It was furnished with a microwave and a dorm fridge. I found the tv was a smart tv way late, but I honestly didn't care. Check out is 11. I entered the room thinking it was going to be a simple room, but I was impressed how cute the towels were folded. That extra effort didn't go unnoticed. Plan to visit again. Staff was nice especially since I arrived at 3 a. m. Still respectful and friendly

name: Renee Fanning
text: We (my son and I) have been staying at the Knights Inn since the end of January.  We have and still are enjoying our stay here. The owners are very nice people and the accomdations have been very comfortable.  I myself wold recommend  anyone to stay here if they need a hotel.

name: Jimmy Peterson
text: Good place to go anytime if you need place to stay cheap had no problems everything works free Wi-Fi breakfast on weekdays free parking TV Netflix coffee anything you need shower I would recommend this to anybody who needs a hotel or a place to stay it's awesome place To say ,Room was clean. Nice bed, Nice bath.Was surprised that they have forty inch smart TV's WiFi fast. Was a pleasant stay and a real plus to be able to watch Net Flicks.Close to New York Throughway and next to all the food joints and shopping, Me and my daughter stay here when we come in town the staff is nice and they are very sweet with my child they take time to make us feel important and call us by name as we enter it's a great place to stay nice clean rooms and great rate

name: Jorge Aguilar Segura
text: Great locale for when you want relax and have a little bit of home when you are on the road. Places are accessible, the staff is excellent, and the price is right. The outdoor patio allows for some low key recreation.

name: Tracia Ham
text: Entire hotel only has two bathtubs let's start there. My first room was a closet with a kitchenette and bathroom in it and my "terrace" was a shared courtyard with four other rooms. There is no ice machine. And the hot water is lukewarm...two days worth of lukewarm shower water yet kitchen sink stayed hot. Pots, pans, plates, and silverware were very convenient and free upon request. Jennifer the front desk girl for the mornings was awesome!

name: Ed Padin
text: Nice place. Room was small,  but clean. Cement floors are cold. Weird millenial style decor. Still, it was perfectly serviceable as a place to spend the night. The bed was comfy.

name: J. W.
text: Cute room. Front desk staff couldn't find my reservation...took us over 20 mins to check in. She said she was giving us a room with two queens or a king and a better room for the inconvenience. Got to the room and had one queen, facing busy street. Went down and asked about the beds literally 60 seconds later. She acted like she had never seen me before. Decent hotel, decent location.

name: Marcos Farion Jr.
text: Must be nice in good weather. When it's cold you don't use the outside facilities. Our room supposed to be in upper levels but they got as the ground level. They forgot the housekeeping one day even tho we asked personally (they did it correctly the other days). Everyday is a new person in the front desk, I didn't like that, felt like in a hostel not a hotel. Rooms were clean when we got there, plenty of space to live, cook, etc. Out air conditioner was on the floor, beside the bed, so you can't sleep with the hot air straight to your face. There was no heater in our room (which is weird because the corridor had) just the air conditioner and a small portable heater. The WC is nice but the water does not get hot enough. When it's 30F outside it does make a big difference. TV is nice, a big 55" brand new and good channels. Goos location, at least 4 dofferent metro lines go there as I can remember now. The line 1 RED stops right in front of it. We recommend, but be aware of all above.

name: Douglas Fernandez
text: It was a cool trendy spot. Loads of board games. Had a Shabby Chic aesthetic. Bed wasn't very comfortable. And the only give one towel per person. Felt more like an apartment then a hotel room.

name: DD O
text: Terrific alternative to old downtown brand names. Great loft fun too!

name: Chloe Fuchs
text:
The customer service was alright but new management is clearly needed. The entrance is super sketchy and unless you're from NYC you'd think it was illegitimate. The room took way too long to be cleaned, there was still hair in the shower catch and our toilet was clogged when we got there. When we asked for someone to come up and help, the front door girl showed up with a plunger and meekly handed it to us to do ourselves.

On top of that, who ever hired the contractors to develop this hotel should be sued and then lose their licenses, there was dried grout all over the tiles, holes and pencil markings all over the walls, there are light switches that don't turn anything on and lights that have no switch! Our phone wasn't working so the handy man had to come in and out several times; turns out it wasn't even plugged in. The walls are incredible thin, we could hear someone else's TV blaring from down the hall and the gap between the door and floor is so huge you can see the feet of those who walk by.

The positives, very close to the subway and has a market right next door. The room are a nice space and while there clearly needs to be a management overhaul, it's clear that the front desk staff and handymen have good intentions and were very polite.

text:
Great cheep place to get a good nights sleep.
The Hotel is nothing special and has been around for a long time.
Not everything works. (broken fridge one night)
No bugs :D
clean.
Respectful staff.
Can call 24/7 front desk and will be happy to book additional nights on request.
Pool
The breakfast is skimpy at best. If you are looking for a good complementary meal go elsewhere. If all you need is a Coffey then this is good.
Good location
Across from Aviation mall, and right next to the Silo (breakfast /shop) and is in town.

name: Erik Rist
text: No WiFi, the heater was a bit noisy, but otherwise a decent place for the money. Lots of good restaurants in the area, very close to I87.

name: IRIS A SCHMIDT
text: We stay at Econo Lodge hotels almost everywhere we travel because it is cost effective, the rooms are clean, beds very comfortable and the staff and maintenance are hard working people, like us, who take pride in the service they provide and positively represent the corporation that employs them.  Our stay at the Glens Falls location, unfortunately, fell quite below the standards we are accustomed to with this chain.

name: Jesse Y
text: Needed a last minute stay, the guy at econolodge was incredibly helpful.

name: Joshua Clark
text: Caught some sweet Pokemon in their parking lot.

name: Faded Hatred
text: Absolutely horrendous front desk service. And the rooms my colleague and I had were extremely dirty and smelled of mold. The bexs were horrendous and accomadated by 4 of the smallest pillows we have ever seen. Id never stay there again.

name: Sanjay Huilgol
text:
This review is for Econo Lodge in the Lake George area.
It was not worth the price. Probably the surge pricing was due to long weekend. The wifi was not working. And also, no complimentary breakfast.
TLDR; This should be your last option if you are visiting the Lake George area.
